Name: Description
Foreign Born Population: The foreign-born population includes anyone who was not a U.S. citizen or a U.S. national at birth. This includes individuals who are U.S. citizens by naturalization or not U.S. citizens.

Name: Source Notes
Foreign Born Population: U.S. Census Bureau, American Community Survey 1-Year Estimates, Summary Table B05003 (2005-2021); retrieved from https://data.census.gov/.

Name: Notes
Foreign Born Population:
Percents refer to the percent of the selected age group breakdown.

Please note, we do not report 2020 American Community Survey 1-year estimates. Due to disruptions and biases in data collection during 2020, the Census Bureau released the “experimental” 1-year estimates for 2020 and advises against comparing against estimates from prior or future years.
